id: pm-jqd2
title: pm extension --install pm-<alias> / @unbrained/pm-<alias> fails with 'Local extension source does not exist' instead of suggesting the bundled catalog alias
description: "2026-07-04 sandbox audit #3: 'pm extension install pm-beads' falls through to local-path resolution and errors 'Local extension source does not exist: .../pm-beads'. The bundled catalog alias is 'beads' (install_command 'pm install beads --project'). Agents naturally try the package folder name (pm-beads) or npm name (@unbrained/pm-beads). Fix: before local-path fallback, match the target against bundled catalog aliases, package folder names (pm-<alias>) and npm package names (@unbrained/pm-<alias>); on near-miss emit a did-you-mean with the exact install command."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[4]: agent-ux,audit-followup,extensions,never-block
created_at: "2026-07-04T10:54:17.266Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-06T18:42:58.413Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 90
acceptance_criteria: pm extension --install pm-<alias> and @unbrained/pm-<alias> resolve to the bundled catalog or fail with a suggestion listing catalog aliases; never-block recovery bundle included.
parent: pm-ugqx
risk: low
confidence: high
resolution: "Bundled-source resolution accepts alias/pm-<alias>/@unbrained/pm-<alias>; unmatched bare names emit npm:-prefixed next_best_command plus bundled alias catalog in a never-block recovery bundle."
expected_result: All three spellings of every bundled package install or emit the exact catalog command; unknown names still reach the local-path error with targeted recovery.
actual_result: "Verified end-to-end on fresh temp workspace: pm install pm-kanban + @unbrained/pm-todos install; pm install pm-changelog (npm-only) errors with npm:pm-changelog hint; 116/116 spec tests pass; tsc clean."
comments[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-06T16:56:23.805Z",codex-cli-agent,"Review response: accepted Greptile P2 on bare-name recovery wording. The bundled-alias hint no longer renders misleading 'Known aliases: .' punctuation when no aliases are discovered; focused extension/register/annotation tests pass."
  "2026-07-06T18:33:23.467Z",codex-cli-agent,"Review response: accepted Sourcery feedback on bundled alias discovery cost. Bare local-source miss recovery now caches bundled package aliases after the first lookup, avoiding repeated filesystem/catalog work across multi-target install failures while preserving best-effort fallback behavior. Verification: focused register/extension tests passed (197 tests); pnpm typecheck passed."
  "2026-07-06T18:42:58.412Z",codex-cli-agent,"Review response: accepted Greptile P2 on the bundled-alias cache lifetime. The cache is now keyed by the resolved PM_CLI_PACKAGE_ROOT override, so test/runtime package-root changes refresh alias discovery while repeated misses in one scope still avoid duplicate filesystem scans. Verification: focused register/extension tests passed (197 tests); pnpm typecheck passed."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-06T14:01:21.734Z",maintainer-agent,"2026-07-06 audit #12: reproduced live on v2026.7.6 tarball in CJS sandbox (root 'pm install pm-kanban' same dead-end). Fixed: resolveBundledPackageRoot now matches alias + package directory (pm-<alias>) + npm package name (@unbrained/pm-<alias>), case-insensitive; local-path miss on bare package-ish names now raises code local_source_not_found_bare_name with npm:<name> next_best_command and the bundled alias list. Specs added to extension-command.spec.ts (spellings + bare-name recovery + path-miss stays plain)."
close_reason: fixed
body: "## Context\n2026-07-04 sandbox audit #3: `pm extension install pm-beads` (also @unbrained/pm-beads) falls through to local-path resolution and errors 'Local extension source does not exist: .../pm-beads'. The bundled catalog alias is 'beads' (install_command `pm install beads --project`). Agents naturally try the package folder name or npm name first — never-block demands a mapping, not a dead end.\n\n## Approach\nBefore the local-path fallback in the extension install resolver, match the target against: bundled catalog aliases, package folder names (pm-<alias>), and npm names (@unbrained/pm-<alias>). Exact match → install the catalog alias directly (or emit the exact install command); near-miss → did-you-mean via the existing OSA Damerau suggester.\n\n## Definition of done\nAll three spellings of every bundled package either install or emit the exact catalog command; unknown names still reach the local-path error; spec covers alias, folder-name, npm-name, and near-miss paths."
